HEADWORD: Philogynist
<hw>Phi*log"y*nist</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Philogyny</er>.]</ety> <def>A lover or friend of women; one who
esteems woman as the higher type of humanity; -- opposed to
<ant>misogynist</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Philogyny</ent>⟦br⟧
